ILLEGAL shebeens in northern KZN were raided at the weekend.Cops said five suspects were arrested during the raids in the Nonoti, Thembeni and Maphumulo areas.The suspects were allegedly bust for various offences such as possession of dagga, possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition, as well as dealing in liquor without a licence.KZN police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said the Ilembe task team, Kwadukuza crime intelligence and the national mobile training unit were targeting shebeens and illegal firearms.&ldquo;Three unlicensed firearms and ammunition were recovered. All recovered firearms will be sent for ballistic testing to establish if they were used in any other crime in the province,&rdquo; said Zwane.&ldquo;One shebeen was closed down during the operation. The suspects will appear in different magistrates courts during the course of this week.&rdquo;Acting provincial commissioner, Major-General Bheki Langa, commended the members for a job well done. &ldquo;Such operations will be conducted in other areas in the province to curb violent crime and contact crimes. &ldquo;Those who are dealing in liquor without licences will be visited and charged accordingly.&rdquo;